  <h1 class="gd-h1">Getting to North Iceland</h1>
  <p class="gd-lede">You've booked your heliski week on the Troll Peninsula &mdash; now comes the practical question of how you actually get there. Siglufj&ouml;r&eth;ur sits on Iceland's northern coast, a long way from where your international flight lands, but the journey is straightforward once you understand the shape of it: <strong>fly into Keflav&iacute;k, reach the north, then a short final leg to town</strong>. This is a practical travel-planning guide for booked skiers, covering arrival, onward options, timings and the buffer that makes it all painless. When you're ready to see the trips themselves, browse <a href="/packages">the packages</a> or read up on <a href="/iceland">heliskiing in Iceland</a>.</p>
